/SLLjkWs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>That is the newly- refurbished Music Hall in Cincinnati. It was built in 1878 and of course is extremely beautiful inside. The renovation allowed them to acoustically tune the room to perfection. I have attended Three Star Wars shows- 4,5, and 6 (The Cincinnati Pops plays the soundtrack while the movie plays on a huge screen above them) in exchange for my time taking pictures with fans, they've donated large handfuls of tickets so the families at the Ronald McDonald House can have a night out and forget about their troubles for a while.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/c3NyZHT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is Hannah my contact at FC Cincinnati. Really nice and very professional. The evening went extremely smooth because of all the effort she put into it.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NMlDlqv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I don't have a cat but I can offer a possible substitute. This is a silhouette of young Luke Skywalker. The Newport Aquarium put a bunch of different Star Wars silhouettes on the floors of the aquarium and let the penguins walk through non-toxic paint and then over top of these. The little fuzzy part by Luke's collar, is actually where their cute butt feathers touched the paper. Good night and May The 4th Be With You!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/IDtLLMs</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[imflukeskywalker]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>What the actual f**k America?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/PAvpcce</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/40uQQAL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/PAvpcce</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[chrisbgg]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Hail... equality</title><link